This paper discusses clustering ensemble, which is a subfield of unsupervised learning. The paper also introduces the idea of engaging supervision in the clustering ensemble procedure, which falls under the category of semi-supervised learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DM (Data Mining). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of consensus functions and weighting mechanisms, which are relevant to the sub-categories cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DB (Databases).
